summary: can you write a carol danvers x reader fic where reader is pregnant and carol talks to the baby before missions and the other...
question: can you write a carol danvers x reader fic where reader is pregnant and carol talks to the baby before missions and the other avengers teases her a bit?
answer:
bean

[A/N: I tried something a bit different with this request and i really like it! Please tell me what you think!]

“Hey little one,” Carol whispers into the skin of your swollen belly, “Its mommy. Well, Light-up mommy. I have to go away for a bit now. I’m going to miss you so much. And mommy. Don’t give her too much hassle whilst I’m away! And Bean? I can’t stress this enough, please don’t come out early! Mommy is scarily close to your due date and light-up mommy can’t miss your arrival Angel!”

The sounds of muffled giggles pulls your attention away from your wife’s conversation with your unborn child. Looking up from her, you see the rest of the team stood in the doorway, watching the strongest member of the team crumble to her knees for her baby.

“Yes, other children, what do you want?” Carol asks, a bit annoyed that they interrupted the limited time with her baby. Thor, who looks so happy for his closest friend, turns to glare at the other avengers who can no longer muffle their childish laughter, and answers for them.

“I’m sorry about them, they are childish.”

The team look at Thor like he’s crazy, and Tony says,

“No, we’re laughing because the strongest member of our team, who can literally destroy anyone and anything, is currently lying flat out, resting her head on her wife’s belly, is talking to it, and is completely whipped for a little baby! Seriously, Carol? We thought you were stronger than that”

Carol looks at you with frustration and a hint of sorrow in her eyes. Although she had Maria and Monica, she never felt like she had a real family until she met you. The happiest day of her life was the day you committed to each other wholly, and she knew she had a permanent family. The second happiest day of her life was when you told her your family would be expanding. Although, she is sure this day would be pushed to the third happiest day of her life soon, by the birth of your child. But hearing the people she considered to be her closest friends (besides yourself and Maria) say she isn’t strong because she is giving love to her family hurt her. She sits up from the couch, gives your bean a small pat, sends a half assed smile your way and makes her way out of the room.

Your sad eyes follow her frame, and then turn into a hardened glare when they fall upon the group of supposed heroes, who have hurt the woman you love. You lean forward to stand up, and Thor rushes to your side to assist you. Once you were balanced, you waddled over to stand in front of the group. Thor stood next to you, an angry look on his face as well. He couldn’t believe his ears when he heard Tony say those words to his best friend. The day he found out about Y/N’s pregnancy he was overjoyed for the both of them. Although the other Avengers teased him for being their #1 fan, he will always agree with them. He loves Carol and Y/N together. He knew Carol way before she met Y/N. The pair had become close after the final war with Thanos, and he had noticed something off with her. After the adrenaline of the win, and the parties/celebrations had worn off, she seemed down. And then she met Y/N and he finally realised what was wrong with her, she was lonely.

“I can’t believe you. You know what Carol has been through, and yet you still thought it was okay to talk to her like that? How ignorant do you have to be? This is her first child, a product of our love for each other. So what if she shows a softer side of herself to her family? She is still the strongest Avenger here, sorry Thor,” he nods in understanding, “She needs to make sure the people she loves knows that she does in fact love them. I swear to GOD if you have ruined that for the both of us, and have made her uncomfortable… Carol and I will be taking our business elsewhere, to say the least.”

With the threat of the Avengers losing the strongest member of their team, they seemed to have been slapped in the face with realisation. Each one of them had been through some form of struggle in their lives, and they had all been able to connect with each other in some way about it. They understood the pain of their individual pasts, and the fact that they had just made a fellow team mate feel bad because of their technique of healing from past wounds? They feel horrible. No, worse than that. Tony murmurs something about going to get Carol back and for everyone to stay here and sit down.

Thor assists you back to the couch and leaves a space for Carol to sit next to you. When her and Tony return, the teams gazes fall to the floor in disgrace.

She walks up to you and strokes your hair slightly before sitting next to you.

“Carol, I am so sorry for what i said. It was insensitive and I didn’t think it through. We all know you are the strongest Avenger here, and you could whoop all our asses any day. If you show a softer side to yourself, then hey? who cares? After all, I have a soft side too. I still play Tea parties with Morgan,” He looks around the room before his eyes land on Steve, “So does Steve. We’re both quite soft when it comes to her.”

Clint lifts his gaze to connect with Carols,

“I still play barbie with Cooper and Lila”

Nat joins in as well,

“I watch Barbie movies more than i should”

Carol starts to giggle at this. She looks around the room and sees that they are all truly sorry. Although it hurt her a lot, she knows she can move past it, and continue showering her family with love.

“Thank you all, honestly. I know you didn’t really mean it, and thank you for the honesty with your storie- Baby, why is the couch wet?”

With all the stress of the current situation, you hadn’t noticed the sudden pressure and release in your abdomen, signalling your water breaking. You and Carol share a look of realisation, before squealing. The team kick into action and start shouting stuff like,

“I’ll get the bags!”

“I’ll make sure the room is ready!”

“Carol take her straight to the med-wing, we’ve got everything else”

And of course, Thor joins in with a,

“Why is everyone panicking? It’s just urine?”


~6 hours later~


Carol makes the journey from Y/N’s room down to the meeting room in which the entirety of the Avengers are waiting. A grin is prominent on her face, and she has a slight urgency in her step. She opens the door to the meeting room and meets everyones expectant gazes,

“It’s a girl!”

With all the stress of the current situation, you hadn’t noticed the sudden pressure and release in your abdomen, signalling your water breaking. You and Carol share a look of realisation, before squealing. The team kick into action and start shouting stuff like,

“I’ll get the bags!”

“I’ll make sure the room is ready!”

“Carol take her straight to the med-wing, we’ve got everything else”

And of course, Thor joins in with a,

“Why is everyone panicking? It’s just urine?”


~6 hours later~


Carol makes the journey from Y/N’s room down to the meeting room in which the entirety of the Avengers are waiting. A grin is prominent on her face, and she has a slight urgency in her step. She opens the door to the meeting room and meets everyones expectant gazes,

“It’s a girl!”
